  "prompt": "What is haka?",
  "response": "The haka is a traditional war dance originating from the M\u0101ori people of New Zealand. It is characterized by vigorous movements, loud chanting, stomping of the feet, facial contortions, and other expressions intended to intimidate. Historically, the haka was performed by warriors before a battle as a display of their strength, unity, and determination.\n\nToday, the haka is performed on various occasions, including ceremonies, celebrations, and sporting events. One of the most famous performances of the haka is by the New Zealand national rugby team, the All Blacks, before international matches. The haka has become an iconic symbol of M\u0101ori culture and New Zealand identity.",
